Do endpoints (like this random example[1]) get marked (implicitly) as (request scoped) CDI beans? The use case that I am imagining, that might need clarity in the documentation, is something like this:
@Path("/hello")
public class HelloResource {

    @POST
    @Lock
    public String addCredit() {
        // some write operation
    }
}

and then the @Lock wouldn't work in such cases (for multiple simulatenous requests)?
[1] https://github.com/quarkusio/quarkus/blob/master/extensions/rest-client-jaxb/deployment/src/test/java/io/quarkus/restclient/jaxb/deployment/HelloResource.java
